48    /**
49    * A {@link JSModule} dependency graph that assigns a depth to each module and
50    * can answer depth-related queries about them. For the purposes of this class,
51    * a module's depth is defined as the number of hops in the longest path from
52    * the module to a module with no dependencies.
53    *
54    */
 
93.4% Uncovered Elements: 13 (197) Complexity: 41 Complexity Density: 0.3
55    public class JSModuleGraph {
56   
57    private List<JSModule> modules;
58   
59    /**
60    * Lists of modules at each depth. <code>modulesByDepth.get(3)</code> is a
61    * list of the modules at depth 3, for example.
62    */
63    private List<List<JSModule>> modulesByDepth;
64   
65    /**
66    * dependencyMap is a cache of dependencies that makes the dependsOn
67    * function faster. Each map entry associates a starting
68    * JSModule with the set of JSModules that are transitively dependent on the
69    * starting module.
70    *
71    * If the cache returns null, then the entry hasn't been filled in for that
72    * module.
73    *
74    * dependencyMap should be filled from leaf to root so that
75    * getTransitiveDepsDeepestFirst can use its results directly.
76    */
77    private Map<JSModule, Set<JSModule>> dependencyMap = Maps.newHashMap();
